# AXIOM APEX — Agentic Process Executor

## Enterprise-Grade Parallel Swarm Orchestrator & Deterministic Execution Kernel

[![PyPI Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/pypi-v3.0.1-blue.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/axiom-apex/)
[![Build Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/tests-152%20%2F%20152%20passed-success.svg)](#4-testing--verification)
[![Security Level](https://img.shields.io/badge/security-paranoid%20sandbox-red.svg)](#3-security-sandboxing-paranoid-mode)

Production-ready core execution systems engine for the AXIOM LLC ecosystem. APEX is a stateless, deterministic, highly parallelized runtime that coordinates multi-threaded agent swarms, RSI functionality, automated task planning, and vector-backed RAG execution.

This core repository contains the runtime engine, parallel compilation and retrieval benchmarks, strict state-assertion components, and the structural templates system enabling autonomous business unit generation. All client-facing implementation briefs, interactive voice response (IVR) setups, and logistics dashboards have been decoupled and migrated to the [axiom-demos](https://github.com/axiom-llc/axiom-demos) repository.

---

## 1. System Architecture

The core runtime is strictly organized to isolate system execution, resource adapters, and optimization benchmarks:

```
~/c/axiom-llc/axiom-apex/
├── core/                        # System Kernel
│   ├── api_clients.py           # Provider interface abstractions
│   ├── loop.py                  # Primary state-transition execution loop
│   ├── planner.py               # Hierarchical task-decomposition planner
│   ├── rag.py                   # Stateless contextual chunking & vector search
│   ├── rollback.py              # Transactional failure recovery & state rollback
│   ├── schema.py                # Structured operational type definitions
│   ├── state.py                 # Thread-safe in-memory state tracking
│   ├── swarm.py                 # Multi-agent asynchronous parallel swarm coordinator
│   ├── tools.py                 # Tool registration & binding interfaces
│   ├── trace.py                 # Execution trace-loggers & telemetry
│   ├── types.py                 # Core domain data types
│   └── validator.py             # Sandbox & threat validation layer
├── benchmarks/                  # Evaluation Harnesses
│   ├── eval_rag_dataset.json    # Standard evaluation dataset
│   ├── eval_rag.py              # Precision and recall evaluations for RAG queries
│   ├── parallel_codegen.py      # Multi-threaded code generation performance test
│   ├── tasks.json               # Structured benchmark execution tasks
│   └── results/                 # Evaluation output matrices
├── tests/                       # Regression Test Suite
│   ├── conftest.py              # Pytest fixtures and mocks
│   ├── test_apex.py             # Core state & loop execution checks
│   ├── test_ivr.py              # Asynchronous voice-session transaction checks
│   ├── test_policy.py           # Regulatory boundary policy evaluations
│   ├── test_rag.py              # Vector retrieval assertions
│   └── testdata/                # Policy and FAQ baseline documents
├── templates.json               # Autonomous Business Unit Schema Catalog
├── templates.py                 # Dynamic Template Loader & Assembler
├── server.py                    # REST API Server Daemon
├── mcp.py                       # Model Context Protocol adapter
├── llm.py                       # LLM connector layer
├── paranoid.py                  # Low-overhead security configuration
├── toolloader.py                # Dynamic external tool integration
└── pyproject.toml               # Package build metadata & dependencies
```

---

## 2. Dynamic Business Templates (`templates.json`)

`templates.json` is a core component of the AXIOM APEX engine, enabling the programmatic generation and instant initialization of autonomous commercial units. Coupled with `templates.py`, the system maps standardized business profiles to structured execution guidelines, tracking metrics, specialized tools, and target operating rates:

```json
{
  "solo_agency": {
    "name": "Solo Consulting Agency Lifecycle",
    "description": "Automated life-cycle: Lead qualification, structured proposals, metric-driven delivery, invoicing, and receivable tracking",
    "required_data": ["~/agency/leads/", "~/agency/proposals/", "~/agency/projects/", "~/agency/invoices/"]
  },
  "compliance_audit": {
    "name": "Regulatory Compliance & Security Audit",
    "description": "Daily automated posture spot-checks and full framework audits (SOC 2, HIPAA, PCI-DSS, GDPR)",
    "required_data": ["~/compliance/evidence/", "~/compliance/findings/", "~/compliance/reports/"]
  },
  "venture_bootstrap": {
    "name": "Venture Bootstrapping & Market Validation",
    "description": "Automated market-sizing, tech stack alignment analysis, MVP specification, and cold outreach composition",
    "required_data": ["~/ventures/"]
  },
  "healthcare_rcm": {
    "name": "Healthcare Revenue Cycle Management (RCM)",
    "description": "Automated accounts receivable aging analysis, claim intake scrubs, and denial appeal generation",
    "required_data": ["~/rcm/claims/", "~/rcm/denials/", "~/rcm/ar/"]
  },
  "due_diligence": {
    "name": "Investment & M&A Due Diligence",
    "description": "Parallel multi-agent research across financial, legal, technology, and regulatory dimensions with red-flag reporting",
    "required_data": ["~/diligence/"]
  }
}
```

This catalog allows the primary execution kernel (`core/loop.py`) to instantly specialize the task-planning engine (`core/planner.py`) and validator constraint-limits (`core/validator.py`) for specific corporate functions.

---

## 3. Security & Sandboxing (Paranoid Mode)

To protect host infrastructure against remote code execution, pipeline tampering, and data exfiltration inside autonomous swarms, AXIOM APEX implements a low-latency sandboxing model:

1.  **Strict Sanitization**: The `core/validator.py` module evaluates all planner actions against a compiled regular expression blocklist (`_BLOCK_PATTERNS`).
2.  **Explicit Consent**: Execution parameters restrict arbitrary subprocess launches and filesystem directory traversals unless explicitly initialized in non-paranoid developer environments.
3.  **Daemon Containment**: Swarm instances are restricted to standard working patterns:

```bash
# Start the API daemon with full sandbox constraints enabled
apex serve --paranoid

# Run local business tasks in a strictly contained runtime sandbox
apex run --paranoid
```

---

## 4. Testing & Verification

The core AXIOM APEX engine enforces strict regression barriers. The test suite contains 152 deterministic verification modules covering the central state machine, concurrent swarm locks, automated policy evaluations, and stateless vector retrieval.

The verification suite evaluates:
*   Memory lock integrity and state transition safety boundaries.
*   Automated regulatory compliance scans and legal conflict scrubbing.
*   Telephony IVR mocks and simulated multi-agent transaction workflows.
*   Stateless RAG query routing and vector space retrieval latency.

To verify system stability and execute all 152 tests, run the following command within the repository root:

```bash
pytest tests/
```

### Expected Output Trace
```
=========================== 152 passed in 118.25s ===========================
```

